---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="About | AI Experiments"
  description="Learn more about this projects and research blog"
>
  <div class="container">
    <article class="about-content">
      <h1 class="title">About</h1>
      
      <div class="content">
        <p class="lead">
          Welcome to my research blog, a collection of projects, experiments, and observations 
          across security, software, and intelligent systems.
        </p>
        
        <h2>What You'll Find Here</h2>
        <p>
          This blog documents hands on technical work, from small proof of concept projects 
          to deeper investigations into how real systems behave, fail, and interact in practice. 
          Each post focuses on what I learned, what worked, what did not, and why that matters.
        </p>
        
        <h2>The Approach</h2>
        <p>
          I value both theory and practice. Understanding concepts at a deep level is just as 
          important to me as testing them in real systems, so this blog reflects a mix of 
          analytical thinking and hands-on exploration. I study the ideas behind these technologies, 
          then examine how they behave when built, stressed, or applied in real contexts.

          Topics range from security engineering and system behavior to theoretical models, 
          machine learning concepts, automation, and tooling. The goal is always to draw out clear, 
          practical insights while also appreciating the underlying principles that shape how these systems work.
        </p>
        
        <p>
          Topics range from security engineering and system behavior to applications of machine learning, 
          automation, and tooling. The emphasis is always on practical insight that you can apply in your 
          own projects or research.
        </p>
        
        <h2>Connect</h2>
        <p>
          If you are interested in discussing these projects, security and AI, or possible collaborations, 
          feel free to reach out or explore the work shared here.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .container {
    max-width: 750px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 4rem 2rem;
  }
  
  .about-content {
    animation: fadeInUp 0.6s ease-out;
  }
  
  @keyframes fadeInUp {
    from {
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(20px);
    }
    to {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: translateY(0);
    }
  }
  
  .title {
    font-size: 4rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-text) 0%, var(--color-primary) 100%);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
  }
  
  .content {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }
  
  .lead {
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  
  .content h2 {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
  
  .content p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  
  .cta {
    margin-top: 4rem;
    padding-top: 3rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }
  
  .btn {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: white;
    padding: 1rem 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-weight: 600;
    transition: var(--transition);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 12px rgba(240, 93, 35, 0.2);
  }
  
  .btn:hover {
    background: var(--color-primary-dark);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: 0 6px 20px rgba(240, 93, 35, 0.3);
    color: white;
  }
  
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .container {
      padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
    }
    
    .title {
      font-size: 2.5rem;
    }
    
    .lead {
      font-size: 1.2rem;
    }
    
    .content {
      font-size: 1rem;
    }
  }
</style>
